USING TigerVNC TO REMOTE DESKTOP INTO RASPBERRY PI

Both pi and client computer must be tethered via ethernet or connected to the same private wifi (use phone hotspot, not school wifi)

Open TigerVNC Desktop application
Type in hostname or IP address (found by typing "hostname -I" into Pi terminal)
 - example hostname from DRAGON: dragon.local
 - example IP address from DRAGON: 172.27.32.41
 - if IP address changes, go google how to set a static IP address for a given wifi network on the Pi
Click "yes" as many times as it pops up
Enter username and password for pi (find username by typing "whoami" into Pi terminal)
 - example username and password from DRAGON:
 	- u: dragon
 	- p: dragon
 	
 	
TROUBLESHOOTING
If TigerVNC fails to connect and freezes, open terminal and type:

- ps aux | grep vncviewer

look for the PID, which is the first 4 digit number. Then type:

- kill <PID>
